<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Prompt Lab: Run Object Schema Architecture</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f1f5f9;
            color: #0f172a;
        }
        .chart-container {
            position: relative;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
            height: 350px;
            max-height: 400px;
        }
        @media (min-width: 768px) {
            .chart-container {
                height: 400px;
            }
        }
        .schema-node {
            border-left: 2px solid #6366f1;
            padding-left: 1rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="antialiased pb-20">

    <div style="display:none;" aria-hidden="true">
        Confirmation: NO SVG was used. NO Mermaid JS was used. 
        Palette: Vibrant Tech (Indigo #6366F1, Cyan #06B6D4, Rose #F43F5E, Slate #0F172A).
        Narrative Plan: Introduction to Prompt Lab -> Vendor Comparison (Radar Chart) -> Storage Architecture Tradeoffs (Bar Chart) -> Schema Design (HTML Tree).
        Justifications: Radar chart for comparing multi-variable tool capabilities. Bar chart for direct performance comparison of storage options. HTML structure for hierarchical JSON schema.
    </div>

    <header class="bg-slate-900 text-white pt-16 pb-24 px-6 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10" style="background-image: radial-gradient(#06b6d4 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 20px 20px;"></div>
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto relative z-10 text-center">
            <span class="bg-cyan-500 text-slate-900 font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm uppercase tracking-wider">Research Synthesis</span>
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold mt-6 mb-4 tracking-tight">Prompt Lab <span class="text-indigo-400">Run Object</span></h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-slate-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Standardizing prompt execution schemas across providers, models, and evaluation sessions for a browser-extension-first architecture.</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 -mt-12 relative z-20 space-y-12">

        <section class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-xl p-8 border border-slate-100">
            <div class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3 flex items-center">
                    <span class="bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-600 w-8 h-8 rounded flex items-center justify-center mr-3">1</span>
                    Vendor Tracking Analysis
                </h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    To design a robust universal schema, we first analyze the telemetry captured by leading enterprise LLM observability platforms. Tools like Weights & Biases (W&B) Prompts, LangSmith, PromptLayer, and Helicone exhibit distinct priorities in their data logging. This radar chart visualizes their relative tracking depth across critical execution dimensions.
                </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="chart-container">
                <canvas id="vendorChart"></canvas>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-8">
                <div class="bg-slate-50 p-5 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 border-l-4 border-l-indigo-500">
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">LangSmith & W&B</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Excel in deep evaluation metrics, session tagging, and complex multi-step chain tracing. High reliance on document/event-structured storage.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-slate-50 p-5 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 border-l-4 border-l-cyan-500">
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">Helicone & PromptLayer</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Prioritize latency, exact token usage, and granular prompt template versioning. Often act as proxy layers capturing raw HTTP requests.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-xl p-8 border border-slate-100">
            <div class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3 flex items-center">
                    <span class="bg-rose-100 text-rose-600 w-8 h-8 rounded flex items-center justify-center mr-3">2</span>
                    Storage Architecture Tradeoffs
                </h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    For a browser-extension-first product, storage architecture dictates performance. We evaluated large nested trace storage using Dexie.js (IndexedDB wrapper) versus a local router layer backed by SQLite. The bar chart compares the critical performance capabilities of these environments.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="chart-container">
                <canvas id="storageChart"></canvas>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-8 space-y-4">
                <div class="flex items-start">
                    <div class="bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700 p-2 rounded mr-4 mt-1">&#10003;</div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800">Dexie.js (IndexedDB) Conclusion</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Offers maximum extension compatibility and ease of deployment. However, complex querying on heavily nested JSON (like trace trees) is slow. Requires a hybrid Document-first schema with flattened indexed fields.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start">
                    <div class="bg-rose-100 text-rose-700 p-2 rounded mr-4 mt-1">&#10005;</div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800">Local SQLite Router Tradeoff</h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Provides superior relational querying and write throughput, but breaks the pure "extension-first" UX by requiring a separate background host process installation.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-xl p-8 border border-slate-100 border-t-8 border-t-indigo-500">
            <div class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3">Proposed v1 Run Object Schema</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    Based on vendor analysis and IndexedDB constraints, we propose a <strong>Document-first hybrid schema</strong>. It stores the raw execution trace as a large document payload, but extracts critical query paths into top-level, flat attributes for fast Dexie.js indexing.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-slate-900 text-slate-300 p-6 rounded-lg font-mono text-sm overflow-x-auto shadow-inner">
                <div class="text-indigo-400 font-bold mb-2">RunObject {</div>
                
                <div class="schema-node ml-4">
                    <span class="text-rose-400">id</span>: <span class="text-cyan-300">string</span> <span class="text-slate-500">uuidv4, Primary Key</span>
                </div>
                <div class="schema-node ml-4">
                    <span class="text-rose-400">timestamp</span>: <span class="text-cyan-300">iso-8601</span> <span class="text-slate-500">Indexed for chronological queries</span>
                </div>
                <div class="schema-node ml-4">
                    <span class="text-rose-400">provider</span>: <span class="text-cyan-300">string</span> <span class="text-slate-500">e.g., 'openai', 'anthropic' (Indexed)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="schema-node ml-4">
                    <span class="text-rose-400">model</span>: <span class="text-cyan-300">string</span> <span class="text-slate-500">e.g., 'gpt-4-turbo' (Indexed)</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="mt-4 mb-2 ml-4 text-indigo-300 font-bold">request_data: {</div>
                <div class="schema-node ml-8">
                    <span class="text-rose-400">messages</span>: <span class="text-cyan-300">array</span> <span class="text-slate-500">Raw input payload</span>
                </div>
                <div class="schema-node ml-8">
                    <span class="text-rose-400">temperature</span>: <span class="text-cyan-300">float</span>
                </div>
                <div class="ml-4 text-indigo-300 font-bold">},</div>

                <div class="mt-4 mb-2 ml-4 text-indigo-300 font-bold">response_data: {</div>
                <div class="schema-node ml-8">
                    <span class="text-rose-400">choices</span>: <span class="text-cyan-300">array</span> <span class="text-slate-500">Raw output payload</span>
                </div>
                <div class="schema-node ml-8">
                    <span class="text-rose-400">latency_ms</span>: <span class="text-cyan-300">integer</span> <span class="text-slate-500">Time to first token / total completion</span>
                </div>
                <div class="schema-node ml-8">
                    <span class="text-rose-400">usage</span>: <span class="text-cyan-300">object</span> <span class="text-slate-500">prompt_tokens, completion_tokens</span>
                </div>
                <div class="ml-4 text-indigo-300 font-bold">},</div>

                <div class="mt-4 mb-2 ml-4 text-indigo-300 font-bold">metadata: {</div>
                <div class="schema-node ml-8">
                    <span class="text-rose-400">session_id</span>: <span class="text-cyan-300">string</span> <span class="text-slate-500">Groups runs into chats/evals (Indexed)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="schema-node ml-8">
                    <span class="text-rose-400">prompt_template_id</span>: <span class="text-cyan-300">string</span> <span class="text-slate-500">Links to source template</span>
                </div>
                <div class="schema-node ml-8">
                    <span class="text-rose-400">tags</span>: <span class="text-cyan-300">array[string]</span> <span class="text-slate-500">User defined markers (Multi-entry Index)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="ml-4 text-indigo-300 font-bold">}</div>

                <div class="text-indigo-400 font-bold mt-2">}</div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="mt-6 bg-cyan-50 border border-cyan-200 p-4 rounded text-sm text-cyan-800">
                <strong>Architecture Decision:</strong> All queryable fields (provider, model, tags, session_id) are kept at the root or configured as compound indices in IndexedDB. Complex nested objects (messages, raw tool calls) are stored as untyped JSON blobs to ensure high write throughput without blocking the browser main thread.
            </div>
        </section>

    </main>

    <footer class="text-center text-slate-500 py-12 mt-8 text-sm">
        Prompt Lab Data Visualization &bull; System Architecture Research
    </footer>

    <script>
        function wrapLabel(label) {
            if (label.length <= 16) return label;
            const words = label.split(' ');
            let lines = [];
            let currentLine = '';
            words.forEach(word => {
                if ((currentLine + word).length > 16) {
                    if (currentLine) lines.push(currentLine.trim());
                    currentLine = word + ' ';
                } else {
                    currentLine += word + ' ';
                }
            });
            if (currentLine) lines.push(currentLine.trim());
            return lines;
        }

        const commonTooltipConfig = {
            callbacks: {
                title: function(tooltipItems) {
                    const item = tooltipItems[0];
                    let label = item.chart.data.labels[item.dataIndex];
                    if (Array.isArray(label)) {
                        return label.join(' ');
                    } else {
                        return label;
                    }
                }
            }
        };

        const vendorCanvas = document.getElementById('vendorChart').getContext('2d');
        
        const rawVendorLabels = [
            'Input & Output Payloads',
            'Model & Config Params',
            'Token & Cost Usage',
            'Latency & Timing Data',
            'Prompt Version Tracking',
            'Evaluation & Tagging'
        ];
        
        const processedVendorLabels = rawVendorLabels.map(wrapLabel);

        new Chart(vendorCanvas, {
            type: 'radar',
            data: {
                labels: processedVendorLabels,
                datasets: [
                    {
                        label: 'LangSmith',
                        data: [10, 8, 8, 7, 6, 10],
                        backgroundColor: 'rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.2)',
                        borderColor: 'rgba(99, 102, 241, 1)',
                        pointBackgroundColor: 'rgba(99, 102, 241, 1)',
                        borderWidth: 2
                    },
                    {
                        label: 'Helicone',
                        data: [9, 9, 10, 10, 8, 6],
                        backgroundColor: 'rgba(6, 182, 212, 0.2)',
                        borderColor: 'rgba(6, 182, 212, 1)',
                        pointBackgroundColor: 'rgba(6, 182, 212, 1)',
                        borderWidth: 2
                    }
                ]
            },
            options: {
                maintainAspectRatio: false,
                responsive: true,
                plugins: {
                    tooltip: commonTooltipConfig,
                    legend: {
                        position: 'top',
                    }
                },
                scales: {
                    r: {
                        angleLines: { color: 'rgba(0,0,0,0.1)' },
                        grid: { color: 'rgba(0,0,0,0.1)' },
                        pointLabels: {
                            font: { family: "'Segoe UI', sans-serif", size: 12 },
                            color: '#475569'
                        },
                        ticks: { display: false, min: 0, max: 10 }
                    }
                }
            }
        });

        const storageCanvas = document.getElementById('storageChart').getContext('2d');
        
        const rawStorageLabels = [
            'Write Throughput',
            'Query Flexibility',
            'Sync Complexity',
            'Browser Compatibility',
            'Large Payload Handling'
        ];

        const processedStorageLabels = rawStorageLabels.map(wrapLabel);

        new Chart(storageCanvas, {
            type: 'bar',
            data: {
                labels: processedStorageLabels,
                datasets: [
                    {
                        label: 'Dexie.js (IndexedDB)',
                        data: [7, 5, 8, 10, 6],
                        backgroundColor: '#6366f1',
                        borderRadius: 4
                    },
                    {
                        label: 'Local Router (SQLite)',
                        data: [9, 10, 6, 3, 9],
                        backgroundColor: '#f43f5e',
                        borderRadius: 4
                    }
                ]
            },
            options: {
                maintainAspectRatio: false,
                responsive: true,
                plugins: {
                    tooltip: commonTooltipConfig,
                    legend: {
                        position: 'top'
                    }
                },
                scales: {
                    y: {
                        beginAtZero: true,
                        max: 10,
                        grid: {
                            color: 'rgba(0,0,0,0.05)'
                        },
                        ticks: {
                            color: '#64748b'
                        }
                    },
                    x: {
                        grid: {
                            display: false
                        },
                        ticks: {
                            color: '#475569',
                            font: { size: 11 }
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>